text: Dickson Wamwiri Wanjiku (December 24, 1984 - September 6, 2020) was a Kenyan taekwondo practitioner. Wamwiri qualified for the men's 58 kg class at the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing, after winning the championship title from the African Qualification Tournament in Tripoli, Libya. Wamwiri died on September 6, 2020 from cardiac arrest in Nairobi at the age of 35.Decorated Kenyan taekwondo star collapses and dies in Nairobi ==References== Category:1984 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Deaths from cardiac arrest Category:Olympians for Kenya Category:Taekwondo practitioners
